/target
*.mind
*.mind-wal
# Python bindings build/test scaffolding (bindings/python): the local venv and
# pytest/maturin caches are throwaway (wheels themselves are ignored below).
.venv/
__pycache__/
.pytest_cache/
fuzz/target
fuzz/artifacts
# The Python bindings are their own workspace with its own target/; the crate is
# excluded from the root workspace, so the root /target rule does not cover it.
# `maturin build --out dist` (the release workflow's command) lands wheels in
# dist/, so both are throwaway build output.
bindings/python/target
bindings/python/dist
# Materialized benchmark datasets are large build products regenerated from the
# committed specs (benches/src/dataset.rs), never committed themselves.
benches/data/
# Harness output. `latest.md` is a scratch render; per-version result JSONs are
# published only when a release is cut (docs/BENCHMARKS.md §4 rule 3) by
# force-adding the specific file — the dev-run noise stays out of the tree.
benches/results/
